1
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:07,359
- Thank you.
- Would you like something else?

2
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:10,320
No. No, no, not just yet. I'm waiting.

3
00:01:11,363 --> 00:01:12,656
I'm expecting someone.

4
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:01,496
Would this be
one of your regular haunts?

5
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:04,082
I don't have any regular haunts.

6
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:16,887
Let me see it.

7
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,899
Sometimes I imagine
I still feel it around my neck.

8
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:31,652
I carried it for so many years.

9
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:34,154
How does it feel around yours?

10
00:02:35,656 --> 00:02:38,116
We can free each other of it.

11
00:02:42,788 --> 00:02:45,791
Love to chatter, don't they,
our muggle friends.

12
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,294
Though one must admit,
they make a good cup of tea.

13
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:53,173
What you're doing is madness.

14
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:56,635
It's what we said we'd do.

15
00:02:57,469 --> 00:02:59,846
- I was young. I was...
- Committed.

16
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:01,390
To me.

17
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,017
To us.

18
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:10,190
I went along because...

19
00:03:11,817 --> 00:03:13,026
Because?

20
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:15,278
Because I was in love with you.

21
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:18,156
Yes.

22
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:22,494
But that's not why you went along.

23
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,997
It was you who said
we could reshape the world.

24
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:28,834
That it was our birthright.

25
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:51,898
Can you smell it? The stench.

26
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:58,238
Do you really intend
to turn your back on your own kind?

27
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,031
For these animals?

28
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:06,204
With or without you,
I'll burn down their world, Albus.

29
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,125
There's nothing you can do to stop me.

30
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:16,089
Enjoy your cup of tea.

31
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,374
She's ready.

32
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:15,625
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

33
00:06:45,697 --> 00:06:46,865
Beautiful.

34
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,619
All right, you two.

35
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,663
Now, the tricky bit.

36
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,367
Accio.

37
00:09:16,848 --> 00:09:18,349
I'm so sorry.

38
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,303
Twins.

39
00:09:57,722 --> 00:09:59,390
You had twins.

40
00:12:25,328 --> 00:12:26,746
Leave us.

41
00:12:29,332 --> 00:12:30,583
Show me.

42
00:12:40,802 --> 00:12:43,137
The others, they said it was special.

43
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:45,682
Ooh, it's beyond special.

44
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:47,976
See?

45
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:50,353
See its eyes?

46
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,231
Those eyes see everything.

47
00:12:55,858 --> 00:13:00,571
When a qilin is born, a righteous leader
will rise to change our world forever.

48
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:08,121
Her birth brings change,
credence, to everything.

49
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:11,541
You did well.

50
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:17,588
Rest.

51
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,552
There.

52
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:07,513
There.

53
00:14:43,674 --> 00:14:46,737
I don't suppose you'd like to
tell me what this is about, would you?

54
00:14:46,761 --> 00:14:49,764
He just asked that we meet,
and that I be sure to bring you.

55
00:14:49,931 --> 00:14:50,932
Hmm.

56
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:52,100
Right.

57
00:15:06,489 --> 00:15:09,534
Here to meet my brother, I expect.

58
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:12,453
No, sir.
We're here to see Albus Dumbledore.

59
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:18,960
- That would be my brother.
- Oh.

60
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,838
Sorry. I'm, um... brilliant.

61
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,798
I'm newt scamander,
and this is theseus...

62
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,259
Up the stairs. First on the left.

63
00:15:38,813 --> 00:15:40,653
Has newt told you
why you're here?

64
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:42,567
Was he meant to?

65
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,528
No. As a matter of fact.

66
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:50,116
There's something that we, uh...

67
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:53,161
That, uh, Dumbledore
wishes to speak to you about.

68
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,163
It's a proposal.

69
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,126
All right.

70
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:04,857
You know what this is, of course.

71
00:16:04,881 --> 00:16:06,257
Newt had it in Paris.

72
00:16:07,175 --> 00:16:10,052
I can't say I have
much experience with such things,

73
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:11,888
but it looks to me to be a blood troth.

74
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:14,599
That would be correct.

75
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:17,393
And whose blood is contained within?

76
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:19,437
Mine.

77
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:21,564
And Grindelwald's.

78
00:16:25,485 --> 00:16:27,379
I'm assuming that's why
you can't move against him?

79
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:28,403
Yes.

80
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,823
Nor he against me.

81
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,411
Can I ask, what would possess you
to make such a thing?

82
00:16:36,579 --> 00:16:37,914
Love.

83
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:42,293
Arrogance. Naiveté. Pick your poison.

84
00:16:43,753 --> 00:16:46,714
We were young,
we were going to transform the world.

85
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:47,965
Mm.

86
00:16:48,049 --> 00:16:52,094
This ensured that we would,
even if one of us had a change of heart.

87
00:16:52,178 --> 00:16:55,765
And what would happen
if you were to fight him?

88
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:08,861
It's really quite beautiful,
you have to admit.

89
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:15,952
Were I to even think about defying it...

90
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:29,549
It knows, you see.

91
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:35,763
Albus.

92
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:38,057
It senses the betrayal in my heart.

93
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,475
Albus.

94
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:45,105
Albus.

95
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:59,412
That would be the least of it.

96
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:08,838
Young man's magic,
but as you can see...

97
00:18:10,006 --> 00:18:11,549
Powerful magic.

98
00:18:15,011 --> 00:18:16,971
It can't be undone.

99
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:26,439
So this proposal, I take it
the qilin has something to do with it?

100
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,190
He promises he won't tell a soul.

101
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:33,404
Ifwe're to defeat him,

102
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:35,740
the qilin's only part of it.

103
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,910
The world as we know it
is coming undone.

104
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:45,875
Gellert's pulling it apart
with hate, bigotry.

105
00:18:48,711 --> 00:18:53,799
Things that seem unimaginable today
will seem inevitable tomorrow...

106
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:55,968
If we don't stop him.

107
00:18:57,803 --> 00:19:00,306
Should you agree to do what I ask...

108
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,100
You'll have to trust me.

109
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:06,562
Even when every instinct
tells you not to.

110
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:17,823
Let's hear it.

111
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:47,561
Does he send you to spy on me?

112
00:19:50,523 --> 00:19:52,358
But he asks.

113
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,610
What ya thinkin', what ya feeling.

114
00:19:54,694 --> 00:19:56,946
And the others?

115
00:19:57,029 --> 00:19:59,031
Does he ask what
they're thinking and feeling?

116
00:19:59,115 --> 00:20:02,660
Yes, but it's mostly you.

117
00:20:03,536 --> 00:20:05,037
And do you tell him?

118
00:20:07,498 --> 00:20:09,417
You do.

119
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:13,295
Who's reading whose mind now?

120
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:22,346
Tell me what you see.

121
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:26,892
You're a Dumbledore.

122
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:30,813
It's an important family.

123
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:33,607
You know this because he's told you.

124
00:20:35,818 --> 00:20:38,696
He's also told you they abandoned you.

125
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:42,992
That you were a...
A dirty secret.

126
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,205
Um... he says
Dumbledore abandoned him too,

127
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:50,207
and he knows how you feel.

128
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,419
And for that reason...

129
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:56,088
He's asked you to kill him.

130
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:01,802
I want you to go now, queenie.

131
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:07,391
I don't tell him.

132
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:11,061
Not always.

133
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:14,940
Not everything.

134
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:25,970
Hey, we're...

135
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:30,516
Queenie.

136
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:32,017
Hi, sweetie.

137
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:41,777
Honey...

138
00:22:41,861 --> 00:22:43,529
Look at your bakery.

139
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:45,656
It's like a ghost town.

140
00:22:46,866 --> 00:22:48,576
Yeah, well, I missed you.

141
00:22:48,659 --> 00:22:50,411
On, baby.

142
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,080
Why don't you come here?

143
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:55,457
Come here.

144
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:03,048
Hey.

145
00:23:06,176 --> 00:23:09,388
Everything's gonna be all right.

146
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:13,684
Everything's gonna be just fine.

147
00:23:40,461 --> 00:23:43,839
Hey, sweetheart,
what brings you downtown?

148
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:48,510
I really hope you didn't spend all day
coming up with that.

149
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:53,390
Oh, you want scary,
is that what you want?

150
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:58,312
You know what it is,
you just aren't menacing enough.

151
00:23:58,395 --> 00:24:02,232
I think I'm plenty menacing.

152
00:24:03,192 --> 00:24:05,194
Am I not menacing?

153
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:09,198
Maybe if you waved your arms around,
you know, like a crazy man,

154
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:11,742
then you'd appear more menacing.

155
00:24:16,956 --> 00:24:19,625
That's good. A little more.

156
00:24:22,378 --> 00:24:24,254
A little more.

157
00:24:24,338 --> 00:24:26,215
Keep going. Perfect.

158
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:29,760
Three, two, one.

159
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:36,684
That's enough. Get outta here.

160
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:38,686
What's on your mind, baker boy?

161
00:24:38,769 --> 00:24:39,937
Ah, jeez.

162
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,689
You should be ashamed of yourselves.

163
00:24:41,772 --> 00:24:42,856
Oh, well, we're not.

164
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:44,358
It's a lady.

165
00:24:46,068 --> 00:24:47,903
I tell you what...

166
00:24:47,987 --> 00:24:49,507
I'll give you the first shot.
Go ahead.

167
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:50,572
You sure?

168
00:24:50,656 --> 00:24:53,033
Oh, boy.

169
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:03,419
Last time
I ever help that woman out again.

170
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:04,545
Lallyl

171
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:07,423
whoopsie, frank.
Sometimes I forget my own strength.

172
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:09,842
I'll take it from here.
Thank you!

173
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:10,843
Welcome.

174
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:13,178
- Catch you later, lally.
- Bye, Stanley.

175
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:15,142
I'll be over for a game
of befudler Dudley soon.

176
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:16,890
All right.

177
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:19,393
That's my cousin Stanley. He's a wizard.

178
00:25:20,477 --> 00:25:23,147
Please! It's early,
don't make me work for it.

179
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:24,582
I said I wanted out, and I want out.

180
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:25,691
Come now, Mr. Kowalski.

181
00:25:25,774 --> 00:25:28,235
Can't believe my therapist said
you wizards don't exist.

182
00:25:28,318 --> 00:25:30,654
What a waste of money!

183
00:25:30,738 --> 00:25:33,032
You do know I'm a witch, right?

184
00:25:33,907 --> 00:25:34,825
Yeah.

185
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:36,410
Look_.

186
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:38,120
You seem like a really nice witch.

187
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:40,181
You don't know what
I've been through with you people.

188
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:43,667
So, could you please get out of my life?

189
00:25:45,669 --> 00:25:47,796
- A little over a year ago...
- Oh, my...

190
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,524
In the hopes of securing
a small business loan,

191
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:51,609
you walked through the doors
of the steen national bank

192
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:54,011
located about six blocks from here.

193
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,739
You then made the acquaintance
of newt scamander,

194
00:25:55,763 --> 00:25:59,558
the world's foremost and,
albeit only, magizoologist.

195
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:00,702
You then learned of a world

196
00:26:00,726 --> 00:26:02,478
you had previously
been wholly unaware of.

197
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:05,147
You met and fell in love
with a witch named queenie Goldstein,

198
00:26:05,230 --> 00:26:07,191
had your brain wiped
by means of obliviation,

199
00:26:07,274 --> 00:26:08,817
only it didn't take.

200
00:26:08,901 --> 00:26:11,487
And as a result, you reunited
with Ms. Goldstein who,

201
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:14,156
after your refusal to marry her, mm,

202
00:26:14,782 --> 00:26:17,993
decided to join gellert Grindelwald
and his dark army of followers,

203
00:26:18,077 --> 00:26:19,495
who pose the single greatest threat

204
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:22,247
to both your world and ours
in four centuries.

205
00:26:22,331 --> 00:26:23,874
How did I do?

206
00:26:23,957 --> 00:26:25,375
That was good.

207
00:26:26,001 --> 00:26:28,712
Except for the part about queenie
going over to the dark side.

208
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:33,509
I mean, yeah, she's cuckoo.

209
00:26:33,592 --> 00:26:36,095
But she's got a heart
bigger than this whole crazy island,

210
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:38,055
and she's so smart, you know?

211
00:26:38,138 --> 00:26:39,949
She can legitimately
read your brain, you know,

212
00:26:39,973 --> 00:26:41,100
she's a whatchamacallit...

213
00:26:41,183 --> 00:26:43,143
- A legilimens.
- Yeah.

214
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:48,065
Look...

215
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:53,821
You see this?

216
00:26:53,904 --> 00:26:57,282
You see the pan?
That's me, I'm the pan.

217
00:26:57,741 --> 00:27:00,619
I'm all dented, dime-a-dozen.
I'm just a schmo.

218
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:03,431
I don't know what kind of crazy ideas
you have in your head there, lady,

219
00:27:03,455 --> 00:27:05,833
but I'm sure as hell
you could do a lot better than me.

220
00:27:05,916 --> 00:27:07,084
Goodbye.

221
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,545
I don't think we can, Mr. Kowalski.

222
00:27:11,547 --> 00:27:14,383
You could have ducked under the counter,
but you didn't.

223
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:17,553
You could have looked the other way,
but you didn't.

224
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:18,679
In fact,

225
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:22,724
you were willing to put yourself
in danger to save a perfect stranger.

226
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:24,184
Seems to me

227
00:27:24,268 --> 00:27:27,020
you're just the kind of average Joe
the world needs right now.

228
00:27:27,604 --> 00:27:29,439
You just don't know it yet.

229
00:27:29,523 --> 00:27:31,733
That's why I had to show you.

230
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:37,406
We need you, Mr. Kowalski.

231
00:27:43,287 --> 00:27:44,621
All right.

232
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:46,623
Call me Jacob.

233
00:27:46,707 --> 00:27:47,791
Call me lally.

234
00:27:47,875 --> 00:27:49,126
-Lally.

235
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:50,460
I gotta lock up.

236
00:27:56,008 --> 00:27:56,884
Thanks.

237
00:27:56,967 --> 00:27:58,635
Much better, Jacob.

238
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:11,190
I believe you know
how this works, Jacob.

239
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:12,274
Mm.

240
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:48,393
What did they say at the ministry?

241
00:28:48,477 --> 00:28:49,853
Liu or Santos?

242
00:28:50,354 --> 00:28:52,648
Officially,
the ministry takes no position.

243
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:57,152
Unofficially, smart money's on Santos.

244
00:28:57,236 --> 00:28:59,446
Although anyone
would be better than Vogel.

245
00:28:59,529 --> 00:29:00,781
Anyone?

246
00:29:04,243 --> 00:29:06,745
I don't believe
he's on the ballot, kama.

247
00:29:06,828 --> 00:29:08,997
He also happens to be a fugitive.

248
00:29:09,081 --> 00:29:10,499
Is there a difference?

249
00:29:13,043 --> 00:29:15,420
Spinning! Always with the spinning.

250
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:16,504
Jacob.

251
00:29:17,506 --> 00:29:19,174
Welcome. You brilliant man.

252
00:29:19,258 --> 00:29:20,550
Sorry.

253
00:29:20,634 --> 00:29:23,262
I was absolutely sure
that professor Hicks would convince you.

254
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:24,680
Yeah.

255
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:28,725
You know me, pal. I can't pass up
a good portkey.

256
00:29:29,518 --> 00:29:31,311
Mr. Scamander.

257
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:32,895
Professor Hicks.

258
00:29:32,938 --> 00:29:34,138
- At long last.
- At long last.

259
00:29:35,274 --> 00:29:38,568
So, professor Hicks and I,
we've corresponded for many years,

260
00:29:38,652 --> 00:29:39,903
but we've never actually met.

261
00:29:39,987 --> 00:29:42,406
So, her book on advanced charm casting
is a must-read.

262
00:29:42,489 --> 00:29:43,824
Newt is far too kind.

263
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:46,910
Fantastic beasts is required reading
for all my fifth years.

264
00:29:47,619 --> 00:29:49,454
Now, let me make some introductions.

265
