Anything you can do to scotch that
will be greatly appreciated.

532
00:49:57,912 --> 00:49:58,912
It's my pleasure.

533
00:49:58,954 --> 00:50:00,372
I shall welcome the challenge.

534
00:50:00,456 --> 00:50:02,917
Besides, I'll have Jacob with me.

535
00:50:03,626 --> 00:50:04,668
Oh, not to worry.

536
00:50:04,752 --> 00:50:08,047
Professor Hicks's defensive magic
is superb.

537
00:50:08,881 --> 00:50:10,174
Until next time.

538
00:50:10,257 --> 00:50:11,800
Such a flatterer.

539
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:14,678
Well, not really. It is superb.

540
00:50:15,471 --> 00:50:16,722
Albus!

541
00:50:16,805 --> 00:50:18,641
I was just wondering...

542
00:50:21,185 --> 00:50:22,186
Yes.

543
00:50:23,854 --> 00:50:25,272
- The case.
- Yes.

544
00:50:25,356 --> 00:50:28,192
Rest assured, it's in safe hands.

545
00:50:41,914 --> 00:50:43,165
Can I help you?

546
00:50:43,374 --> 00:50:45,334
Yes.

547
00:50:45,417 --> 00:50:48,295
I'd like to have this case
replicated, please.

548
00:50:48,754 --> 00:50:49,922
Certainly.

549
00:50:51,715 --> 00:50:54,718
Oh. No, you mustn't open it.

550
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:58,847
Um, I mean, it's not necessary.

551
00:50:59,557 --> 00:51:01,559
The interior isn't important.

552
00:51:02,685 --> 00:51:05,980
I see no reason I can't make you one.

553
00:51:19,076 --> 00:51:20,327
If you leave it here.

554
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:21,787
Oh. No...

555
00:51:22,121 --> 00:51:24,373
I couldn't leave it.

556
00:51:25,165 --> 00:51:27,918
And I'll be needing more than one.

557
00:51:28,752 --> 00:51:30,421
You see, um...

558
00:51:31,505 --> 00:51:35,009
My husband,
He's a bit absentminded.

559
00:51:35,092 --> 00:51:37,011
He's always forgetting things.

560
00:51:37,094 --> 00:51:39,096
Just the other day,
he forgot he was married to me.

561
00:51:41,599 --> 00:51:44,018
Can you imagine?

562
00:51:48,022 --> 00:51:49,773
But I love him.

563
00:51:50,941 --> 00:51:53,360
Exactly how many were you thinking?

564
00:51:54,945 --> 00:51:56,363
Half a dozen,

565
00:51:56,447 --> 00:51:59,116
and I'll need them in two days' time.

566
00:52:07,291 --> 00:52:09,418
Show your hands.

567
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:16,008
Who are you?

568
00:52:16,884 --> 00:52:18,677
My name is Yusuf kama.

569
00:52:20,346 --> 00:52:21,847
Who's our visitor?

570
00:52:21,930 --> 00:52:23,265
I'm an admirer.

571
00:52:23,974 --> 00:52:26,060
You murdered his sister.

572
00:52:26,935 --> 00:52:28,812
Her name was leta.

573
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:32,191
Leta Lestrange.

574
00:52:32,733 --> 00:52:34,443
Ah, yes.

575
00:52:34,526 --> 00:52:36,695
You and your sister
share an ancient bloodline.

576
00:52:36,779 --> 00:52:38,197
Shared.

577
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:40,157
That's the only thing we shared.

578
00:52:41,408 --> 00:52:44,662
Dumbledore sent you, am I right?

579
00:52:45,454 --> 00:52:47,790
He fears
you're in possession of a creature.

580
00:52:48,582 --> 00:52:50,751
He fears the use you may put it to.

581
00:52:51,710 --> 00:52:53,921
He sent me here to spy on you.

582
00:52:55,964 --> 00:52:58,050
What would you like me to tell him?

583
00:53:00,803 --> 00:53:01,970
Queenie.

584
00:53:03,347 --> 00:53:05,432
Is he telling the truth?

585
00:53:18,237 --> 00:53:19,530
What else?

586
00:53:19,613 --> 00:53:21,448
Even though he believes in you,

587
00:53:21,532 --> 00:53:24,326
he holds you responsible
for his sister's death.

588
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:28,330
He carries
her absence with him every day.

589
00:53:30,124 --> 00:53:33,335
Every breath he takes
is a reminder that she breathes no more.

590
00:53:35,129 --> 00:53:36,547
Then I presume you won't mind

591
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:38,632
if I relieve you
of your sister's memory.

592
00:53:44,096 --> 00:53:45,264
Right?

593
00:53:46,390 --> 00:53:47,599
Right.

594
00:54:09,496 --> 00:54:10,622
There.

595
00:54:12,166 --> 00:54:13,751
Better?

596
00:54:15,002 --> 00:54:16,503
Ithoughtso.

597
00:54:16,587 --> 00:54:21,008
When we allow ourselves to be consumed
by anger, the only victim is ourself.

598
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:26,221
Now, we were just about to depart.

599
00:54:26,305 --> 00:54:28,098
Perhaps you'd like to join us?

600
00:54:28,766 --> 00:54:33,103
Come, we can talk some more
about our mutual friend, Dumbledore.

601
00:54:41,862 --> 00:54:43,238
After you.

602
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:12,703
Hello, credence.

603
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:23,964
Do you know
what it's like to have no one?

604
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:26,216
To always be alone?

605
00:56:27,509 --> 00:56:28,760
It's you.

606
00:56:31,722 --> 00:56:34,683
You're the one sending messages
in the mirror.

607
00:56:35,934 --> 00:56:37,644
I'm a Dumbledore.

608
00:56:38,312 --> 00:56:40,272
You abandoned me.

609
00:56:41,732 --> 00:56:45,777
The same blood
that runs my veins runs yours.

610
00:56:55,454 --> 00:56:57,623
He's not here for you.

611
00:56:57,706 --> 00:56:59,249
He's here for me.

612
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:48,882
Things are not quite
what they appear, credence...

613
00:57:49,633 --> 00:57:52,010
No matter what you've been told.

614
00:57:54,262 --> 00:57:55,681
My name is aurelius.

615
00:57:56,098 --> 00:57:57,557
He's lied to you.

616
00:57:57,641 --> 00:57:59,017
Kindled your hate.

617
00:58:59,703 --> 00:59:02,289
What he's told you isn't true...

618
00:59:04,124 --> 00:59:06,668
But we do share the same blood.

619
00:59:07,961 --> 00:59:10,630
You are a Dumbledore.

620
00:59:23,935 --> 00:59:26,021
I'm sorry for your pain.

621
00:59:26,730 --> 00:59:29,357
We didn't know, I promise.

622
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:07,062
No entrance! Access prohibited!

623
01:00:23,829 --> 01:00:25,580
I've come to see my brother.

624
01:00:25,664 --> 01:00:27,582
His name is theseus scamander.

625
01:00:36,383 --> 01:00:37,843
Sorry, that's, uh...

626
01:00:39,886 --> 01:00:41,304
Wand.

627
01:00:56,444 --> 01:00:57,612
Oh, that's, uh...

628
01:00:57,696 --> 01:00:59,990
I'm... I'm a magizoologist.

629
01:01:00,991 --> 01:01:02,271
He's perfectly harmless. He's...

630
01:01:02,951 --> 01:01:04,703
He's just a pet, really.

631
01:01:06,663 --> 01:01:08,331
Sorry.

632
01:01:11,251 --> 01:01:12,460
That's Teddy.

633
01:01:12,544 --> 01:01:14,337
He's a total nightmare, truth be told.

634
01:01:14,421 --> 01:01:15,922
They stay here.

635
01:01:37,694 --> 01:01:39,905
So, how will I know where to find him?

636
01:01:40,572 --> 01:01:41,907
He's your brother?

637
01:01:42,991 --> 01:01:44,201
Yes.

638
01:01:44,284 --> 01:01:46,912
He will be the one
who looks like your brother.

639
01:01:51,333 --> 01:01:53,001
I will be back, pick.

640
01:01:53,418 --> 01:01:54,711
On my word.

641
01:02:01,092 --> 01:02:02,719
"I'll be back, pick.

642
01:02:02,802 --> 01:02:05,013
"On my word."

643
01:02:05,597 --> 01:02:09,434
And I'll be minister of magic
one day.

644
01:02:48,473 --> 01:02:50,308
Take us 'round the back.

645
01:02:50,392 --> 01:02:51,559
It's not safe here.

646
01:02:53,353 --> 01:02:54,353
Roll it down.

647
01:02:54,646 --> 01:02:55,897
What?

648
01:02:56,648 --> 01:02:58,191
The window.

649
01:02:58,275 --> 01:02:59,609
Roll it down.

650
01:03:11,871 --> 01:03:13,915
Grindelwald! Grindelwald!

651
01:03:18,086 --> 01:03:19,796
No. No!

652
01:03:28,680 --> 01:03:29,681
Those people...

653
01:03:30,223 --> 01:03:32,350
Aren't suggesting we listen to them.

654
01:03:32,434 --> 01:03:34,436
They aren't asking us to listen.

655
01:03:34,978 --> 01:03:36,438
They're demanding it.

656
01:03:37,439 --> 01:03:41,026
You're actually proposing that
that man be allowed to stand?

657
01:03:41,109 --> 01:03:42,444
Yes.

658
01:03:43,153 --> 01:03:44,529
Yes, let him stand.

659
01:03:48,575 --> 01:03:50,660
Gellert Grindelwald
wants a muggle-wizard war,

660
01:03:50,744 --> 01:03:53,788
and if he gets his wish,
he won't just destroy their world,

661
01:03:53,872 --> 01:03:55,206
he'll destroy ours as well.

662
01:03:55,290 --> 01:03:57,167
Which is why he cannot win.

663
01:03:58,710 --> 01:04:00,378
Let him stand as a candidate.

664
01:04:00,462 --> 01:04:02,213
Let the people vote.

665
01:04:02,297 --> 01:04:04,424
When he loses,
the people will have spoken.

666
01:04:05,175 --> 01:04:07,844
But deny them their voices,

667
01:04:07,927 --> 01:04:10,597
and those streets will run with blood.

668
01:04:33,787 --> 01:04:34,829
Theseus.

669
01:04:40,085 --> 01:04:41,086
Theseus.

670
01:06:17,682 --> 01:06:18,808
Lally,

671
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:21,019
the guy with the hair...

672
01:06:21,561 --> 01:06:23,813
Sitting next to Edith.

673
01:06:24,397 --> 01:06:26,399
He looks like he can kill somebody.

674
01:06:27,859 --> 01:06:30,111
He also looks like my uncle Dominic.

675
01:06:30,195 --> 01:06:33,823
Is your uncle Dominic
the nonnegian minister of magic?

676
01:06:35,158 --> 01:06:36,659
Didn't think so.

677
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:07,023
Queenie.

678
01:07:08,316 --> 01:07:09,317
Queenie.

679
01:07:19,744 --> 01:07:22,539
Madam Santos, a pleasure.

680
01:07:23,665 --> 01:07:25,792
Your supporters are in fine voice.

681
01:07:25,875 --> 01:07:29,295
As are yours, Mr. Grindelwald.

682
01:07:49,023 --> 01:07:50,525
Rescuing me, are you?

683
01:07:50,608 --> 01:07:52,568
- That's the general idea.
- Huh.

684
01:07:53,069 --> 01:07:55,071
And I presume this...

685
01:07:55,154 --> 01:07:58,116
Whatever it is that you are doing,
is strategic.

686
01:07:58,199 --> 01:08:00,285
Yes, a technique called limbic mimicry.

687
01:08:00,368 --> 01:08:03,788
It discourages violent engagement,
theoretically.

688
01:08:03,871 --> 01:08:06,457
I've only actually ever
attempted it once before.

689
01:08:06,916 --> 01:08:09,877
- And the results?
- Uh...

690
01:08:09,961 --> 01:08:11,254
Inconclusive.

691
01:08:11,796 --> 01:08:13,148
Course that was a laboratory setting

692
01:08:13,172 --> 01:08:15,592
and the conditions
were strictly controlled, and the...

693
01:08:15,675 --> 01:08:17,515
Well, the current conditions
are more volatile,

694
01:08:17,552 --> 01:08:19,613
so making it less predictive
of the ultimate outcome.

695
01:08:19,637 --> 01:08:21,931
The ultimate outcome presumably...

696
01:08:23,016 --> 01:08:27,103
Being our survival.

697
01:09:20,031 --> 01:09:22,575
Well done, come on.

698
01:09:27,955 --> 01:09:29,749
And the plan is?

699
01:09:29,832 --> 01:09:31,000
Hold this.

700
01:09:35,088 --> 01:09:37,090
[{Snonng]

701
01:09:47,016 --> 01:09:48,856
What the bloody hell was that for?

702
01:09:48,893 --> 01:09:50,478
Um...

703
01:09:50,561 --> 01:09:52,188
We're gonna need some help.

704
01:10:01,989 --> 01:10:03,324
Follow me.

705
01:10:08,204 --> 01:10:09,372
Come on.

706
01:10:18,923 --> 01:10:20,717
You're not swiveling properly.

707
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:22,301
Swivel...

708
01:10:22,385 --> 01:10:24,470
Swivel, but delicately.

709
01:10:25,221 --> 01:10:27,640
I'm swiveling
like you're swiveling, newt.

710
01:10:27,724 --> 01:10:29,350
I don't believe you are.

711
01:10:48,661 --> 01:10:49,746
Swivel.

712
01:11:03,134 --> 01:11:04,343
Go to him.

713
01:11:12,685 --> 01:11:13,685
Queenie.

714
01:11:18,232 --> 01:11:19,734
Tell him it's all right.

715
01:11:20,568 --> 01:11:22,153
I can see he's failed.

716
01:11:23,070 --> 01:11:24,655
He'll have another chance.

717
01:11:26,240 --> 01:11:28,785
It's his loyalty I most value.

718
01:12:03,319 --> 01:12:04,612
Stay here.

719
01:12:24,924 --> 01:12:25,925
Oh.

720
01:12:27,218 --> 01:12:28,219
Apologies.

721
01:12:33,850 --> 01:12:34,934
Hmm.

722
01:12:35,852 --> 01:12:37,687
Oh, boy.

723
01:12:54,537 --> 01:12:56,247
Let her go.

724
01:12:56,789 --> 01:12:58,040
Excuse me?

725
01:13:06,924 --> 01:13:09,135
- Assassin!
- Huh?

726
01:17:19,802 --> 01:17:20,802
No, wait.

727
01:17:35,818 --> 01:17:36,818
Newt!

728
01:17:40,531 --> 01:17:41,615
Accio!

729
01:17:42,616 --> 01:17:43,784
Grab the tie.

730
01:18:32,750 --> 01:18:34,251
That was a portkey.

731
01:18:34,919 --> 01:18:35,920
Yeah.

732
01:18:39,131 --> 01:18:40,841
Well done, you two.

733
01:19:05,032 --> 01:19:06,617
Not that either of you asked,

734
01:19:06,700 --> 01:19:08,911
but I would highly recommend
learning charms.

735
01:19:08,994 --> 01:19:09,912
Lally.

736
01:19:09,995 --> 01:19:11,413
What kept you two?

737
01:19:11,538 --> 01:19:14,416
Uh, we encountered
some complications. You?

738
01:19:14,541 --> 01:19:17,461
We encountered some complications.

739
01:19:21,674 --> 01:19:23,467
Jacob tried to murder Grindelwald?

740
01:19:23,550 --> 01:19:25,427
It's a long story.

741
01:19:25,511 --> 01:19:27,263
Is it really snakewood?

742
01:19:27,346 --> 01:19:29,056
Yes, it's really snakewood.

743
01:19:29,556 --> 01:19:31,892
- Can I...
- Mm-mm.

744
01:19:32,351 --> 01:19:33,852
Very dangerous.

745
01:19:34,520 --> 01:19:35,521
It's very powerful.

746
01:19:36,105 --> 01:19:38,565
It's rare. If it got in the wrong hands,
you know...

747
01:19:38,649 --> 01:19:39,692
Mess you up.

748
01:19:39,775 --> 01:19:41,402
Where did you get it?

749
01:19:42,444 --> 01:19:44,113
I got it for Christmas.

750
01:19:44,196 --> 01:19:45,281
Jacob,

751
01:19:45,364 --> 01:19:46,657
look who I found.

752
01:19:46,740 --> 01:19:47,825
Hey.

753
01:19:47,908 --> 01:19:50,286
It's my wizard friends,
newt and theseus.

754
01:19:50,369 --> 01:19:52,746
We're like this, okay,
and that's me right there.

755
01:19:52,830 --> 01:19:55,165
I gotta go. All right, have fun.

756
01:19:55,874 --> 01:19:57,459
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

757
01:19:58,210 --> 01:19:59,420
Can you believe this place?

758
01:19:59,503 --> 01:20:00,814
They got pint-sized little
witches and wizards

759
01:20:00,838 --> 01:20:01,898
running around here.

760
01:20:01,922 --> 01:20:03,173
You don't say.

761
01:20:03,882 --> 01:20:05,175
I was the assassin.

762
01:20:05,843 --> 01:20:07,678
Newt and theseus both went to Hogwarts.

763
01:20:07,761 --> 01:20:09,864
Oh, I knew that.
Well, they're being very nice to me.

764
01:20:09,888 --> 01:20:11,848
The Slytherin boys over there,
they gave me these.

765
01:20:11,890 --> 01:20:13,726
They're delicious. Who wants one?

766
01:20:14,351 --> 01:20:16,645
I never cared for cockroach clusters
much myself,

767
01:20:16,729 --> 01:20:19,273
although honeydukes
are supposed to be the best.

768
01:20:24,987 --> 01:20:26,155
Off you go.

769
01:20:26,905 --> 01:20:27,948
McGonagall.

770
01:20:28,657 --> 01:20:29,783
Albus.

771
01:20:29,867 --> 01:20:30,868
Well done.

772
01:20:30,951 --> 01:20:32,578
All of you, well done.

773
01:20:32,661 --> 01:20:33,579
Congratulations.

774
01:20:33,662 --> 01:20:35,372
-Congratulations? 4ndeed.

775
01:20:35,456 --> 01:20:38,709
Professor Hicks managed
to foil an assassination.

776
01:20:39,376 --> 01:20:41,920
And you are alive and you are well.

777
01:20:42,004 --> 01:20:44,882
The fact that everything didn't go
precisely to plan

778
01:20:44,965 --> 01:20:46,258
was precisely the plan.

779
01:20:46,342 --> 01:20:47,760
Countersight 101.

780
01:20:47,843 --> 01:20:50,304
Albus, forgive me,
but aren't we back where we started?

781
01:20:50,387 --> 01:20:53,182
Actually, I would argue
that things are...

782
01:20:53,265 --> 01:20:55,434
A great deal worse.

783
01:20:57,561 --> 01:20:58,937
You haven't told them, have you?

784
01:21:00,356 --> 01:21:03,233
Grindelwald's been allowed
to stand in the election.

785
01:21:04,234 --> 01:21:05,569
- What?
- But how?

786
01:21:06,153 --> 01:21:09,782
Because Vogel chose easy over right.

787
01:21:32,346 --> 01:21:33,347
Hmm.

788
01:21:34,681 --> 01:21:35,681
It's all right.

789
01:21:36,016 --> 01:21:37,226
Bhutan.

790
01:21:37,309 --> 01:21:39,311
Correct. Three points to hufflepuff.

791
01:21:39,812 --> 01:21:43,774
The kingdom of Bhutan
sits high in the eastern himalayas.

792
01:21:43,857 --> 01:21:47,653
It's a place of indescribable beauty.

793
01:21:47,736 --> 01:21:51,240
Some of our most important magic
has its origins there.

794
01:21:51,323 --> 01:21:56,286
They say if you listen carefully enough,
the past whispers to you.

795
01:21:57,579 --> 01:22:00,124
It also happens to be
where the election will be held.

796
01:22:00,207 --> 01:22:01,542
He can't win, can he?

797
01:22:01,625 --> 01:22:04,002
Only a few days ago
he was a fugitive from justice.

798
01:22:04,086 --> 01:22:09,550
Now he is an official candidate in the
international confederation of wizards.

799
01:22:11,427 --> 01:22:14,430
Dangerous times favor dangerous men.

800
01:22:16,598 --> 01:22:20,102
By the way, we'll be dining
with my brother in the village.

801
01:22:20,185 --> 01:22:23,063
Should you need anything before then,
Minerva is here.

802
01:22:23,897 --> 01:22:25,899
Dumbledore has a brother?

803
01:22:29,111 --> 01:22:30,195
Huh.

804
01:22:44,209 --> 01:22:45,294
Here we are.

805
01:22:49,756 --> 01:22:51,383
Bunty, you're here.

806
01:22:51,467 --> 01:22:52,551
Yes.

807
01:22:54,303 --> 01:22:55,429
How is she?

808
01:22:55,512 --> 01:22:56,555
Oh, she's fine.

809
01:22:57,598 --> 01:22:58,640
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

810
01:22:58,724 --> 01:23:00,350
What's Alfie done now?

811
01:23:00,434 --> 01:23:02,745
Wait, you've not been biting
Timothy's bottom again, have you?

812
01:23:02,769 --> 01:23:07,274
Miss broadacre, I trust my brother
has been a gracious host?

813
01:23:07,858 --> 01:23:09,985
Yes, ever so gracious.

814
01:23:10,110 --> 01:23:11,653
I'm delighted to hear.

815
01:23:11,737 --> 01:23:15,282
Uh, so, rooms have been
arranged for you in the village

816
01:23:15,365 --> 01:23:18,869
and aberforth here
will prepare you a delicious dinner,

817
01:23:18,952 --> 01:23:20,537
his own recipe.

818
01:23:26,710 --> 01:23:29,213
There's more of that if you want it.

819
01:23:33,634 --> 01:23:34,927
Thank you.

820
01:23:35,677 --> 01:23:36,762
Thanks.

821
01:23:40,098 --> 01:23:41,391
Astonishing.

822
01:23:41,475 --> 01:23:44,770
Never has something that looks
so repellent tasted so delicious.

823
01:23:44,853 --> 01:23:46,939
Who is this little one?

824
01:23:47,022 --> 01:23:48,023
Do you mind?

825
01:23:48,815 --> 01:23:50,651
She's a qilin, Jacob.

826
01:23:50,734 --> 01:23:52,569
She's incredibly rare.

827
01:23:52,653 --> 01:23:55,155
One of the most beloved creatures
in the wizarding world.

828
01:23:57,157 --> 01:23:59,326
'Cause she can see into your soul.

829
01:23:59,409 --> 01:24:00,619
Oh. Oh!

830
01:24:02,621 --> 01:24:04,206
You're kidding me.

831
01:24:04,289 --> 01:24:10,212
No. So, if you are good and worthy,
then she'll see that.

832
01:24:10,295 --> 01:24:14,049
But if, on the other hand,
you're cruel and deceitful,

833
01:24:14,132 --> 01:24:16,009
then she'll know that too.

834
01:24:16,760 --> 01:24:18,262
Oh, yeah?

835
01:24:18,345 --> 01:24:20,931
Does she just tell you that
or...

836
01:24:21,890 --> 01:24:23,141
Not exactly tells.

837
01:24:23,225 --> 01:24:28,063
Well, she bows, but only in the presence
of someone truly pure of heart.

838
01:24:30,190 --> 01:24:31,817
I mean,
almost none of us are, of course,

839
01:24:31,900 --> 01:24:34,403
no matter how good of a person
one tries to be.

840
01:24:35,571 --> 01:24:38,615
There was actually a time,
many, many years ago,

841
01:24:38,699 --> 01:24:41,118
when the qilin chose who'd lead us.

842
01:24:43,078 --> 01:24:44,329
No...

843
01:24:44,413 --> 01:24:47,499
Whoa. Woop. Whoa...

844
01:24:49,001 --> 01:24:51,378
Okay. All right, already.

845
01:24:54,339 --> 01:24:55,339
Here you go.

846
01:24:56,425 --> 01:24:57,426
Thriving.

847
01:24:57,509 --> 01:24:59,052
He's just hungry. Look at him.

848
01:24:59,136 --> 01:25:01,616
- She really likes you, Jacob.
- Oh, all right.

849
01:25:04,433 --> 01:25:05,434
It's okay.

850
01:25:14,985 --> 01:25:16,361
Come with me.

851
01:25:18,030 --> 01:25:19,489
I'll help you.

852
01:25:21,325 --> 01:25:23,368
He's your son, aberforth.

853
01:25:26,204 --> 01:25:27,748
He needs you.

854
01:25:40,969 --> 01:25:42,095
Newt.

855
01:25:54,816 --> 01:25:55,942
Come in.

856
01:25:56,610 --> 01:26:00,364
Albus, the mirror downstairs,
there's a message.

857
01:26:00,447 --> 01:26:01,448
Close the door.

858
01:26:09,289 --> 01:26:11,291
It's from credence, newt.

859
01:26:14,503 --> 01:26:17,339
The summer gellert and I fell in love...

860
01:26:18,131 --> 01:26:20,008
My brother fell in love as well,

861
01:26:20,092 --> 01:26:22,386
with a girl from the hollow.

862
01:26:23,595 --> 01:26:25,180
She was sent away.

863
01:26:26,973 --> 01:26:29,351
There were rumors about a child.

864
01:26:31,269 --> 01:26:32,145
Credence...

865
01:26:32,229 --> 01:26:33,730
He's a Dumbledore.

866
01:26:36,983 --> 01:26:39,152
If I'd been a better friend...

867
01:26:40,195 --> 01:26:42,322
To aberforth,
if I'd been a better brother...

868
01:26:43,865 --> 01:26:45,867
He might have confided in me.

869
01:26:47,452 --> 01:26:49,121
Perhaps things
would have been different,

870
01:26:49,204 --> 01:26:50,747
and this boy...

871
01:26:51,456 --> 01:26:54,334
Could have been part of our lives,
part of our family.

872
01:27:00,006 --> 01:27:03,301
Credence can't be saved,
I know you know that.

873
01:27:04,469 --> 01:27:07,973
But he may yet be able to save us.

874
01:27:14,396 --> 01:27:15,689
Phoenix ash.

875
01:27:16,732 --> 01:27:20,110
The bird comes to him
because he's dying, newt.

876
01:27:21,194 --> 01:27:22,863
I know the signs.

877
01:27:23,739 --> 01:27:25,073
You see...

878
01:27:26,908 --> 01:27:30,203
My sister was an obscurial.

879
01:27:31,121 --> 01:27:34,249
And like credence,
she never learned to express her magic.

880
01:27:35,667 --> 01:27:38,545
Over time it grew darker
and began to poison her.

881
01:27:40,088 --> 01:27:43,467
Worst of all, none of us
were capable of easing her pain.

882
01:27:47,137 --> 01:27:49,389
Can you tell me how it is that...

883
01:27:50,098 --> 01:27:52,017
Or how it came to an end for her?

884
01:27:55,270 --> 01:27:58,690
Gellert and I had made plans
to go away together.

885
01:28:00,275 --> 01:28:03,487
My brother didn't approve.

886
01:28:03,570 --> 01:28:05,781
One night, he confronted us.

887
01:28:06,323 --> 01:28:08,784
Voices were raised, threats made.

888
01:28:08,867 --> 01:28:12,329
Aberforth drew his wand,
which was foolish.

889
01:28:15,081 --> 01:28:18,335
I drew my wand,
which was even more foolish.

890
01:28:20,837 --> 01:28:22,798
Gellertjust laughed.

891
01:28:23,965 --> 01:28:26,593
No one heard Ariana
coming down the stairs.

892
01:28:29,721 --> 01:28:32,057
Can't say for certain it was my...

893
01:28:33,642 --> 01:28:34,643
Spell.

894
01:28:39,815 --> 01:28:41,525
Doesn't really matter.

895
01:28:42,275 --> 01:28:46,112
One minute she was there,
and the next she was gone.

896
01:28:47,197 --> 01:28:48,949
I'm so sorry, Albus.

897
01:28:51,243 --> 01:28:54,704
But if it's of any comfort,
perhaps she was saved some pain...

898
01:28:56,414 --> 01:28:58,458
Don't disappoint me, newt.

899
01:28:59,626 --> 01:29:01,336
You of all people.

900
01:29:02,712 --> 01:29:05,006
Your honesty is a gift...

901
01:29:07,175 --> 01:29:09,719
Even if at times a painful one.

902
01:29:14,724 --> 01:29:17,936
Our friends downstairs will be tired
and wanting to go home.

903
01:29:18,019 --> 01:29:20,230
You should... you should go.

904
01:29:34,035 --> 01:29:37,581
Albus, lally said something earlier

905
01:29:37,664 --> 01:29:40,625
about most of us
being ultimately imperfect.

906
01:29:42,127 --> 01:29:46,047
But even if we make mistakes,
terrible things...

907
01:29:47,674 --> 01:29:50,176
We can try to make things right.

908
01:29:52,762 --> 01:29:54,389
And that's what matters...

909
01:29:58,101 --> 01:29:59,603
Trying.

910
01:30:15,577 --> 01:30:16,786
We're with you.

911
01:30:17,495 --> 01:30:18,580
Thank you.

912
01:30:27,172 --> 01:30:29,883
Our time is close,
my brothers and sisters.

913
01:30:30,926 --> 01:30:32,802
Days of hiding are over.

914
01:30:35,430 --> 01:30:37,766
The world will hear our voice.

915
01:30:41,102 --> 01:30:42,604
And it will be deafening.

916
01:30:50,820 --> 01:30:53,657
You didn't come here
to betray Dumbledore...

917
01:30:54,908 --> 01:30:57,577
You know in your pure-blood heart...

918
01:30:59,245 --> 01:31:01,164
Your place is here.

919
01:31:03,375 --> 01:31:06,127
To believe in me
is to believe in yourself.

920
01:31:18,556 --> 01:31:20,850
Prove your loyalty, Mr. Kama.

921
01:31:43,623 --> 01:31:45,500
Vulnera sanentur.

922
01:31:46,126 --> 01:31:50,380
Rennervate vulnera sanentur.

923
01:31:51,339 --> 01:31:56,177
Rennervate vulnera sanentur.

924
01:31:58,596 --> 01:32:04,102
Rennervate vulnera sanentur.

925
01:32:08,982 --> 01:32:09,982
There.

926
01:32:11,568 --> 01:32:12,944
There, there.

927
01:32:14,988 --> 01:32:16,239
There.

928
01:32:18,199 --> 01:32:19,826
Come, look.

929
01:32:23,580 --> 01:32:24,789
Hmm.

930
01:32:25,707 --> 01:32:27,792
This is why we are special.

931
01:32:30,879 --> 01:32:34,674
To conceal our powers
is not merely an affront to ourselves...

932
01:32:36,301 --> 01:32:37,635
It's sinful.

933
01:32:52,275 --> 01:32:53,860
Was there another?

934
01:32:55,111 --> 01:32:56,321
Another?

935
01:32:57,614 --> 01:33:00,617
That night, was there another qilin?

936
01:33:04,329 --> 01:33:05,413
I don't think so...

937
01:33:07,332 --> 01:33:08,792
That's twice you failed me.

938
01:33:08,875 --> 01:33:12,796
Do you not understand
the danger you put me in?

939
01:33:16,633 --> 01:33:18,343
One last chance.

940
01:33:19,010 --> 01:33:20,178
Understood?

941
01:33:23,389 --> 01:33:24,474
Find it.

942
01:34:19,154 --> 01:34:20,572
Hey, newt.

943
01:34:21,447 --> 01:34:23,032
What is this place?

944
01:34:24,033 --> 01:34:26,035
The room we require.

945
01:34:30,456 --> 01:34:34,002
I trust you all have the tickets
that bunty gave you?

946
01:34:34,085 --> 01:34:36,588
You'll need them to
gain access to the ceremony.

947
01:34:36,671 --> 01:34:37,755
What do you think, newt?

948
01:34:37,839 --> 01:34:39,507
Can you tell which one is yours?

949
01:34:41,342 --> 01:34:43,219
Good. I'd be worried if you could.

950
01:34:43,303 --> 01:34:45,555
I assume
the qilin's in one of these cases.

951
01:34:45,638 --> 01:34:46,723
Yes.

952
01:34:46,806 --> 01:34:48,683
- Well, which one is it?
- Which one indeed.

953
01:34:49,142 --> 01:34:51,394
Ooh, it's like
a three-card monte thing.

954
01:34:51,477 --> 01:34:53,313
Like a shell game thing.

955
01:34:53,396 --> 01:34:54,522
Like a short con.

956
01:34:56,566 --> 01:34:58,484
Never mind, it's a muggle thing.

957
01:34:58,568 --> 01:35:00,945
Grindelwald will do anything
within his powers

958
01:35:01,029 --> 01:35:03,364
to get his hands on our rare friend.

959
01:35:03,448 --> 01:35:05,658
Therefore, it's essential that we keep

960
01:35:05,742 --> 01:35:08,912
whoever he dispatches
on his behalf guessing...

961
01:35:09,495 --> 01:35:12,081
So the qilin
gets to the ceremony safely.

962
01:35:12,749 --> 01:35:18,004
If, by teatime, the qilin,
not to mention all of us,

963
01:35:18,922 --> 01:35:20,757
are still alive,

964
01:35:20,840 --> 01:35:23,718
we should consider
our efforts a success.

965
01:35:23,801 --> 01:35:27,138
For the record, nobody ever died
playing three-card monte.

966
01:35:28,890 --> 01:35:30,558
An important distinction.

967
01:35:31,768 --> 01:35:34,520
All right, everybody choose a case
and we'll be on our way.

968
01:35:34,604 --> 01:35:38,274
Mr. Kowalski, you and I
will proceed together first.

969
01:35:44,739 --> 01:35:45,865
Okay.

970
01:36:10,807 --> 01:36:12,868
I'm looking fonnard
to you educating me a little further

971
01:36:12,892 --> 01:36:15,603
on the finer points
of three-card monte.

972
01:36:17,730 --> 01:36:18,731
Mm.

973
01:36:21,442 --> 01:36:22,485
My pleasure.

974
01:36:26,114 --> 01:36:29,951
Well, good luck, everybody.

975
01:36:32,787 --> 01:36:33,787
Good luck.

976
01:36:34,914 --> 01:36:37,625
And you too, bunty girl.

977
01:36:40,503 --> 01:36:41,921
See you, bunty.

978
01:36:56,477 --> 01:36:57,770
It is not lost

979
01:36:57,854 --> 01:37:02,275
on those of us in leadership
that we are currently a world divided.

980
01:37:02,942 --> 01:37:05,987
Each day
brings talk of another conspiracy.

981
01:37:06,696 --> 01:37:08,781
Each hour another dark whisper.

982
01:37:09,324 --> 01:37:12,744
These whispers have
only increased in recent days

983
01:37:13,286 --> 01:37:15,663
with the addition of a third candidate.

984
01:37:16,914 --> 01:37:20,877
There is only one way
to leave absolutely no doubt

985
01:37:21,919 --> 01:37:27,175
that a worthy candidate exists amongst
the three you have been presented.

986
01:37:45,693 --> 01:37:49,781
As every schoolboy and girl knows,

987
01:37:49,864 --> 01:37:56,329
the qilin is the purest of creatures
in our wonderful magical world.

988
01:37:57,080 --> 01:37:58,915
It cannot be deceived.

989
01:38:00,500 --> 01:38:03,086
Let the qilin unite us.

990
01:38:23,481 --> 01:38:25,358
Santos! Santos! Santos!

991
01:38:33,574 --> 01:38:35,576
Santos! Santos! Santos!

992
01:38:37,620 --> 01:38:39,288
Santos! Santos! Santos!

993
01:38:51,509 --> 01:38:52,510
Come.

994
01:38:56,222 --> 01:38:57,974
Where to, next?

995
01:38:58,516 --> 01:39:00,268
Uh, this is where I leave you.

996
01:39:00,810 --> 01:39:03,146
I'm... I'm sorry, you're what?

997
01:39:03,229 --> 01:39:04,647
Leaving me?

998
01:39:04,730 --> 01:39:07,358
I have to meet someone else,
Mr. Kowalski.

999
01:39:07,942 --> 01:39:09,193
Not to worry...

1000
01:39:10,111 --> 01:39:11,612
You'll be perfectly safe.

1001
01:39:15,616 --> 01:39:17,076
You don't have the qilin.

1002
01:39:18,119 --> 01:39:21,038
Feel free to drop the case
at the first hint of trouble.

1003
01:39:21,706 --> 01:39:24,876
One other thing,
if you don't mind me saying.

1004
01:39:24,959 --> 01:39:27,462
You should stop doubting yourself.

1005
01:39:27,545 --> 01:39:30,423
You have something most men
go their entire lives without.

1006
01:39:30,506 --> 01:39:31,924
Do you know what that is?

1007
01:39:33,551 --> 01:39:35,761
A heart that is full.

1008
01:39:36,637 --> 01:39:38,639
Only a truly brave man

1009
01:39:38,723 --> 01:39:43,686
could open himself up
so honestly and completely, as you do.

1010
01:40:12,298 --> 01:40:14,008
Santos! Santos! Santos!

1011
01:40:14,091 --> 01:40:16,928
Santos! Santos! Santos!

1012
01:40:17,011 --> 01:40:20,181
Santos! Santos! Santos!

1013
01:41:27,164 --> 01:41:30,084
Cases, please.

1014
01:41:48,894 --> 01:41:49,894
Hey, fellas.

1015
01:41:54,942 --> 01:41:56,152
Woo-hoo-hoo.

1016
01:41:58,279 --> 01:41:59,947
He's angry.

1017
01:42:15,963 --> 01:42:19,050
Wait. Open them,
make sure it's in there.

1018
01:42:19,133 --> 01:42:20,134
Idiots.

1019
01:44:05,906 --> 01:44:07,366
How long does he have?

1020
01:44:48,657 --> 01:44:50,659
Here. Hey. Hi.

1021
01:44:50,743 --> 01:44:52,036
You're in danger, all right?

1022
01:44:52,119 --> 01:44:53,704
- You need to leave.
- Well...

1023
01:44:54,872 --> 01:44:57,374
I can't... I can't go, okay?

1024
01:44:57,458 --> 01:44:58,834
I can't come home.

1025
01:44:58,918 --> 01:45:00,294
It's too late for me, all right?

1026
01:45:00,377 --> 01:45:02,671
Some mistakes, they're just too big.

1027
01:45:02,755 --> 01:45:04,757
Can you listen to me?

1028
01:45:04,840 --> 01:45:07,051
There's no time. I was followed.

1029
01:45:07,718 --> 01:45:10,763
I gave 'em the slip, but it won't
be long before they find me.

1030
01:45:10,846 --> 01:45:12,406
- They're gonna find us.
- I don't care.

1031
01:45:13,599 --> 01:45:15,184
All I got is us.

1032
01:45:15,267 --> 01:45:16,727
I make no sense without us.

1033
01:45:16,811 --> 01:45:19,647
Jacob, what? Come on...

1034
01:45:19,730 --> 01:45:21,690
I don't love you anymore.
Just get outta here.

1035
01:45:21,774 --> 01:45:24,109
You're the worst liar in the world,
queenie Goldstein.

1036
01:45:25,778 --> 01:45:26,862
You hear that?

1037
01:45:26,946 --> 01:45:28,447
What? No.

1038
01:45:28,531 --> 01:45:30,074
That's a sign.

1039
01:45:30,157 --> 01:45:31,367
Oh, man.

1040
01:45:31,450 --> 01:45:33,369
- Oh, come on.
- Come here, come here.

1041
01:45:33,786 --> 01:45:35,120
Close your eyes.

1042
01:45:36,080 --> 01:45:37,915
Please close your eyes.

1043
01:45:39,625 --> 01:45:41,460
You know what Dumbledore said to me?

1044
01:45:43,712 --> 01:45:46,048
He said that I got a full heart.

1045
01:45:50,177 --> 01:45:51,512
He's wrong.

1046
01:45:52,263 --> 01:45:54,807
I'm always
gonna have room in there for you.

1047
01:45:56,183 --> 01:45:57,309
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1048
01:45:57,393 --> 01:45:58,727
You know it.

1049
01:45:59,895 --> 01:46:01,146
Look at me.

1050
01:46:04,066 --> 01:46:05,651
Queenie Goldstein.

1051
01:47:11,800 --> 01:47:13,177
Mr. Scamander.

1052
01:47:13,260 --> 01:47:15,095
We've never been properly introduced.

1053
01:47:15,179 --> 01:47:18,098
Henrietta fischer...

1054
01:47:18,182 --> 01:47:19,808
Herr Vogel's attaché.

1055
01:47:19,892 --> 01:47:21,977
Ah. Yes, uh,

1056
01:47:22,061 --> 01:47:22,978
hello.

1057
01:47:23,062 --> 01:47:25,105
I can take you up.

1058
01:47:25,940 --> 01:47:28,901
There's a private entrance
for members of the high council.

1059
01:47:29,985 --> 01:47:31,779
If you just follow me.

1060
01:47:31,862 --> 01:47:33,489
I'm sorry, why would you do that?

1061
01:47:34,198 --> 01:47:35,366
Take me up?

1062
01:47:36,075 --> 01:47:38,410
Isn't it obvious?

1063
01:47:38,494 --> 01:47:41,080
No, frankly, it's, uh, not.

1064
01:47:45,668 --> 01:47:47,544
Dumbledore sent me.

1065
01:47:49,672 --> 01:47:53,384
I know what you have
in that case, Mr. Scamander.

1066
01:48:15,030 --> 01:48:16,782
He should be here any minute.

1067
01:49:20,596 --> 01:49:22,014
What kept you?

1068
01:49:36,612 --> 01:49:39,156
I thank
the candidates for their words.

1069
01:49:39,281 --> 01:49:45,579
Each represents a distinct vision
of how we will not shape only our world,

1070
01:49:45,662 --> 01:49:48,165
but the non-magical world as well.

1071
01:49:49,541 --> 01:49:54,671
Which brings us to the most important
part of our ceremony...

1072
01:49:54,755 --> 01:49:56,965
The walk of the qilin.

1073
01:51:26,513 --> 01:51:28,765
The qilin has seen.

1074
01:51:29,850 --> 01:51:31,185
Seen goodness,

1075
01:51:31,685 --> 01:51:33,729
strength...

1076
01:51:33,812 --> 01:51:38,483
Qualities essential
to lead and to guide us.

1077
01:51:40,694 --> 01:51:42,321
Who do you see?

1078
01:51:58,962 --> 01:52:02,925
Gellert Grindelwald is the new leader
of the magical world...

1079
01:52:03,008 --> 01:52:04,718
By acclamation.

1080
01:52:44,174 --> 01:52:46,885
This is the man
who tried to take my life.

1081
01:52:48,053 --> 01:52:52,182
This man, who has no magic...

1082
01:52:53,058 --> 01:52:56,228
Who would marry a witch
and pollute our blood,

1083
01:52:56,311 --> 01:52:59,523
create a forbidden union
that would make us less...

1084
01:53:00,315 --> 01:53:02,359
Make us weak, like his kind.

1085
01:53:04,403 --> 01:53:06,113
He's not alone, my friends.

1086
01:53:07,656 --> 01:53:10,701
There are thousands
who seek to do the same.

1087
01:53:12,452 --> 01:53:15,831
There can only be one response
to such vermin.

1088
01:53:30,095 --> 01:53:31,513
Crucio.

1089
01:53:35,309 --> 01:53:36,977
Make him stop!

1090
01:53:37,602 --> 01:53:42,607
Our war with the Muggles begins today.

1091
01:54:00,167 --> 01:54:01,918
Jacob.

1092
01:54:42,000 --> 01:54:43,835
He's lying to you.

1093
01:54:46,505 --> 01:54:48,715
That creature is dead.

1094
01:54:56,014 --> 01:54:58,266
Not now. Wait.

1095
01:55:03,021 --> 01:55:04,221
He did it to trick you.

1096
01:55:04,689 --> 01:55:07,442
He killed it and bewitched it

1097
01:55:07,526 --> 01:55:10,237
so that
you might think him worthy to lead.

1098
01:55:12,656 --> 01:55:14,783
But he doesn't want to lead you.

1099
01:55:17,369 --> 01:55:19,371
He just wants you to follow.

1100
01:55:20,122 --> 01:55:21,289
Words.

1101
01:55:22,749 --> 01:55:25,085
Words designed to deceive.

1102
01:55:25,794 --> 01:55:28,064
To make you doubt what you've seen
with your own two eyes.

1103
01:55:28,088 --> 01:55:29,690
There were two qilins
born that night.

1104
01:55:29,714 --> 01:55:31,967
A twin. And I know that...

1105
01:55:33,385 --> 01:55:34,511
I know that...

1106
01:55:34,594 --> 01:55:35,720
Because?

1107
01:55:40,058 --> 01:55:42,310
Because you have no proof.

1108
01:55:43,186 --> 01:55:45,272
Because there was no second qilin.

1109
01:55:46,606 --> 01:55:48,024
Am I not right?

1110
01:55:48,108 --> 01:55:49,293
Its mother had been killed, it...

1111
01:55:49,317 --> 01:55:51,862
Then where is it now, Mr. Scamander?

1112
01:56:17,721 --> 01:56:19,890
No one can know everything, newt.

1113
01:56:19,973 --> 01:56:21,183
Remember?

1114
01:56:51,588 --> 01:56:52,923
I don't get it.

1115
01:57:05,143 --> 01:57:07,479
She can't hear you, little one.

1116
01:57:08,980 --> 01:57:10,398
Not here...

1117
01:57:12,192 --> 01:57:14,611
But perhaps somewhere she's listening.

1118
01:57:18,156 --> 01:57:20,492
This is the true qilin.

1119
01:57:21,785 --> 01:57:22,994
Look at it...

1120
01:57:23,537 --> 01:57:25,664
You can see it with your own eyes.

1121
01:57:32,379 --> 01:57:34,923
This can't be allowed to stand.

1122
01:57:35,006 --> 01:57:36,591
The vote must be taken again.

1123
01:57:37,509 --> 01:57:40,178
Come on, Anton. Do something.

1124
01:58:08,540 --> 01:58:09,708
You...

1125
01:58:10,292 --> 01:58:12,043
No, no, no, please.

1126
01:58:37,444 --> 01:58:39,279
I'm honored.

1127
01:58:40,447 --> 01:58:43,575
Butjust as two of you
were born that night,

1128
01:58:43,658 --> 01:58:46,953
there's another here, equally worthy.

1129
01:58:48,413 --> 01:58:50,248
I'm certain of it.

1130
01:59:05,764 --> 01:59:07,098
Thank you.

1131
02:01:59,729 --> 02:02:01,648
Who will love you now, Dumbledore?

1132
02:02:04,692 --> 02:02:06,152
You're all alone.

1133
02:02:56,744 --> 02:02:58,663
I was never your enemy.

1134
02:03:05,920 --> 02:03:08,715
Then, or now.

1135
02:03:49,589 --> 02:03:51,591
Did you ever think of me?

1136
02:03:54,260 --> 02:03:55,511
Always.

1137
02:04:02,894 --> 02:04:04,270
Come home.

1138
02:04:52,777 --> 02:04:55,196
Here she is.

1139
02:04:56,197 --> 02:04:57,865
Well done, bunty.

1140
02:05:01,828 --> 02:05:03,079
Come on, little one.

1141
02:05:04,414 --> 02:05:07,083
I'm sorry.
I must have given you an awful fright.

1142
02:05:07,166 --> 02:05:08,376
No, I think, um...

1143
02:05:08,459 --> 02:05:12,547
Sometimes it takes losing something
to realize quite how much it means.

1144
02:05:15,508 --> 02:05:17,593
And sometimes you just...

1145
02:05:21,139 --> 02:05:23,141
Sometimes you just know.

1146
02:05:33,526 --> 02:05:35,486
Right, in you pop.

1147
02:05:37,739 --> 02:05:39,782
Mr. Kowalski.

1148
02:05:41,242 --> 02:05:43,119
I owe you an apology.

1149
02:05:43,286 --> 02:05:47,749
It... it was never my intent
for you to suffer the cruciatus curse.

1150
02:05:48,791 --> 02:05:50,001
Yeah...

1151
02:05:50,084 --> 02:05:52,462
Well, you know, we got queenie back,
so we're square.

1152
02:05:52,545 --> 02:05:54,589
Hey, can I ask you a question?

1153
02:05:55,548 --> 02:05:57,091
Can I keep this?

1154
02:05:57,175 --> 02:05:58,843
For, like, old times' sake?

1155
02:06:01,387 --> 02:06:05,016
I can't think of anyone more deserving.

1156
02:06:07,351 --> 02:06:08,978
Thanks, professor.

1157
02:06:29,707 --> 02:06:30,792
Remarkable.

1158
02:06:30,875 --> 02:06:31,709
But how?

1159
02:06:31,793 --> 02:06:33,395
I thought you couldn't
move against one another.

1160
02:06:33,419 --> 02:06:34,587
We didn't.

1161
02:06:35,296 --> 02:06:38,132
He sought to kill, I sought to protect.

1162
02:06:38,216 --> 02:06:40,051
Our spells met.

1163
02:06:41,594 --> 02:06:43,471
Let's call it fate.

1164
02:06:44,847 --> 02:06:48,226
After all, how else
will we fulfill our destinies?

1165
02:06:50,103 --> 02:06:51,354
Albus.

1166
02:06:53,147 --> 02:06:54,732
Promise me.

1167
02:06:57,026 --> 02:06:59,070
You'll find him and you'll stop him.

1168
02:07:26,848 --> 02:07:29,809
Albert,
don't forget the pierogis.

1169
02:07:29,892 --> 02:07:31,227
Yes, Mr. K.

1170
02:07:31,310 --> 02:07:32,937
Albert.

1171
02:07:33,020 --> 02:07:35,106
No more than eight minutes
on the kolaczkis.

1172
02:07:35,690 --> 02:07:37,233
Yes, Mr. K.

1173
02:07:37,316 --> 02:07:38,401
He's a sweet kid.

1174
02:07:38,484 --> 02:07:40,945
He doesn't know the difference
between paszteciki and golabki.

1175
02:07:41,028 --> 02:07:42,214
- Hey, sweetheart.
- What?

1176
02:07:42,238 --> 02:07:43,882
Newt doesn't know
what you're talking about.

1177
02:07:43,906 --> 02:07:45,384
I don't know what you're talking about.

1178
02:07:45,408 --> 02:07:48,411
And you are not working today, remember?

1179
02:07:48,494 --> 02:07:49,787
Oh!

1180
02:07:49,871 --> 02:07:51,706
Oh, are you all right, honey?

1181
02:07:51,789 --> 02:07:53,809
Oh, you're nervous about the speech.
Don't be nervous.

1182
02:07:53,833 --> 02:07:54,876
Tell him, honey.

1183
02:07:54,959 --> 02:07:56,103
Don't be nervous about the speech.

1184
02:07:56,127 --> 02:07:57,003
I'm not nervous.

1185
02:07:57,086 --> 02:07:59,213
What is the smell?
Why is there burning?

1186
02:07:59,297 --> 02:08:00,715
Albert?

1187
02:08:02,842 --> 02:08:05,845
Mm. Maybe we're nervous
about something else, huh?

1188
02:08:06,554 --> 02:08:08,764
I can't imagine
what you're talking about.

1189
02:08:09,015 --> 02:08:10,016
Mm-hmm.

1190
02:08:23,279 --> 02:08:25,198
So, the day that I first met Jacob...

1191
02:08:26,532 --> 02:08:27,783
The day that I first met Jacob,

1192
02:08:27,867 --> 02:08:30,161
we were both
sitting in the steen national bank.

1193
02:08:31,954 --> 02:08:33,206
Never would I...

1194
02:08:47,803 --> 02:08:49,722
The maid of honor, I presume?

1195
02:08:51,766 --> 02:08:54,060
The best man, I gather?

1196
02:08:55,937 --> 02:08:58,231
- You've done something to your hair.
- No.

1197
02:09:01,525 --> 02:09:03,778
Well, yes, actually, just...

1198
02:09:03,861 --> 02:09:04,904
Just for tonight.

1199
02:09:04,987 --> 02:09:06,614
- Well, it suits you.
- Thank you, newt.

1200
02:09:12,328 --> 02:09:13,568
- Hello.
- Hi.

1201
02:09:13,621 --> 02:09:14,747
Look who's...

1202
02:09:17,375 --> 02:09:19,252
So good to see you.

1203
02:09:19,335 --> 02:09:20,711
- Hi.
- How are you?

1204
02:09:20,795 --> 02:09:22,004
You look wonderful, lally.

1205
02:09:22,088 --> 02:09:24,340
Well, thank you, newt. I appreciate it.

1206
02:09:24,423 --> 02:09:25,466
Good luck.

1207
02:09:25,549 --> 02:09:26,549
Tina, come on.

1208
02:09:26,592 --> 02:09:28,752
- You must tell me how macusa's been.
- See you inside.

1209
02:09:34,809 --> 02:09:36,686
What about me? How do I look?

1210
02:09:37,019 --> 02:09:38,521
- You all right?
- You look fine.

1211
02:09:38,604 --> 02:09:39,604
You okay?

1212
02:09:39,647 --> 02:09:40,648
Yeah, I'm all right.

1213
02:09:40,731 --> 02:09:42,066
You're not nervous, are you?

1214
02:09:43,442 --> 02:09:46,529
Can't be nervous about
a speech after saving the world. Hmm.

1215
02:10:03,587 --> 02:10:05,131
It's a historic day.

1216
02:10:06,507 --> 02:10:11,053
Where once was before,
there will now be after.

1217
02:10:13,973 --> 02:10:17,810
Funny how historic days seem so ordinary
when you're living them.

1218
02:10:18,894 --> 02:10:21,498
Well, perhaps that's what happens
when the world gets things right.

1219
02:10:21,522 --> 02:10:24,650
Mm, it's jolly nice to know
it happens occasionally.

1220
02:10:28,612 --> 02:10:30,573
I didn't know if I'd see you here.

1221
02:10:31,490 --> 02:10:33,075
I wasn't sure you would, either.

1222
02:10:33,159 --> 02:10:34,469
Hey, newt.

1223
02:10:34,493 --> 02:10:35,493
Yes.

1224
02:10:35,536 --> 02:10:37,496
Jacob seems to think he's lost the ring.

1225
02:10:37,580 --> 02:10:38,748
Please tell me you've got it.

1226
02:10:38,831 --> 02:10:40,750
No, it's all good. Yep.

1227
02:10:40,833 --> 02:10:42,084
Whew!

1228
02:10:42,168 --> 02:10:43,888
That scared me. Jacob!

1229
02:10:46,589 --> 02:10:47,673
Good man, pick.

1230
02:10:52,970 --> 02:10:54,430
I should probably, um...

1231
02:10:56,098 --> 02:10:57,350
Thank you, newt.

1232
02:10:58,934 --> 02:11:00,102
What for?

1233
02:11:00,186 --> 02:11:01,687
Pick your poison.

1234
02:11:03,939 --> 02:11:06,484
I really
couldn't have done it without you.

1235
02:11:13,366 --> 02:11:15,785
I'd do it again, by the way.

1236
02:11:17,578 --> 02:11:19,121
Should you ask.

1237
02:11:34,470 --> 02:11:35,471
Okay.

1238
02:11:37,765 --> 02:11:38,766
Hey.

1239
02:11:49,652 --> 02:11:50,852
- Hey!
- Hello!

1240
02:11:51,028 --> 02:11:52,488
Bunty!

1241
02:11:53,322 --> 02:11:54,865
Bunty!

1242
02:12:14,718 --> 02:12:17,680
Wow, you're so beautiful.

1243
02:12:23,394 --> 02:12:24,603
Oh.

1244
02:12:25,312 --> 02:12:27,356
I can't believe it.

1245
02:12:48,085 --> 02:12:49,628
This is, um... This is Albert.

1246
02:12:49,712 --> 02:12:51,297
I don't know if you've met Albert, yet?

1247
02:12:51,380 --> 02:12:52,756
Have you met lally?

